    [ctns_front]
Linear Function<br/>Intercept-Intercept Form
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
Given the $$x$$-intercept $$(a,0)$$ and the $$y$$-intercept $$(0,b)$$, 
the Intercept-Intercept Form is given by

$|\frac xa + \frac yb = 1, |$

where $$a$$ and $$b$$ are constants.
    [/ctns_back]
    
    [ctns_backspeak]
Given the  x intercept ( a comma 0) and the y  intercept (0 comma b),
the Intercept-Intercept Form is given by the expression

the fraction of x over a plus the fraction of y over b equal to 1,

where a and b are constants.
    [/ctns_backspeak]
    

[/ctns_make]
